node.title: NZ police officer arrested over assault of teenager in Australia
node.description: Police have confirmed that a serving New Zealand officer is facing criminal charges in Canberra, over an alleged indecent assault on a teenager.
node.content:
["", "
no captio Photo: RNZ / Richard Tindiller
", "Ppolice have confirmed that a serving New Zealand officer is facing criminal charges in Canberra, over an alleged indecent assault on a teenager.", "The Canberra Times has identified the accused officer as 66-year-old David Brooke.", "The police said the alleged offending occurred in an international jurisdiction, while the officer was on leave.", "The Canberra Times reported the officer was attending a national football tournament as a referee when the offending occurred.", "They said they are limited in making further comment, as a court process is under way, but an employment process will be carried out."]
